<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" box="[199,520,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,384,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Measurements:</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation box="[438,520,295,321]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,239,459,485]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements of specimens of Cypricercus sp. A., Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov. and Cypricercus tiao sp. nov. Values in brackets are only the lengths of spine (without the length of the valves)." pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Table 1</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,585,331,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Abbreviated diagnosis of female.</emphasis>
LV elongated, with dorsal margin almost straight and parallel to ventral margin; anterior margin less broadly rounded than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martens &amp; Behen" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Klie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[700,839,368,394]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrurus">
<emphasis box="[700,839,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. centrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[920,1032,367,394]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[920,1032,367,394]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1127,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1038,1127,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
RV also with dorsal margin almost straight and largely parallel to ventral margin, posterior spine almost as long as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martens &amp; Behen" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Klie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1158,1298,404,430]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrurus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1298,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. centrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and equally centrally placed in the middle of the caudal margin, slightly pointing upwards, but less robust; almost twice as long as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[209,321,475,502]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[209,321,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[327,415,475,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[327,415,475,501]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Anterior calcified inner margin in both valves about twice the width of that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[1285,1397,475,502]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alfredo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1285,1397,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">C. alfredo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="28" pageNumber="529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
LV overlapping RV on all sides (
<figureCitation box="[574,657,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[293,1294,741,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-247@28.[293,1294,741,1914]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 18. Cypricercus sp. A. Upper Paraná River floodplain. A–F. Female. A. LVi. B. LVi, detail of anterior part. C. LVi, detail of posterior part. D. RVi. E. RVi, detail of anterior part. F. RVi, detail of posterior part. Scale bars: A, D: 1000 µm. B–C, E: 500 µm. F: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4575045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4575045/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,547,573]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Remarks.</emphasis>
We are convinced that this is a representative of a new species in the genus, but as we have only a single female, we will refrain from formally describing it here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="529" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,718]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,507,619,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Ecology and Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Ferreira &amp; Higuti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="2021" box="[514,650,620,646]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypricercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[514,650,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Cypricercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. A was found associated with the root systems of 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1348,620,645]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Eichhornia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azurea">
<emphasis box="[1242,1348,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">E. azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
located in a single lake of the Upper 
<collectingRegion box="[477,553,655,681]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">Paraná</collectingRegion>
River floodplain. Water temperature at time of collecting was 26.3°C; pH was basic (8); electrical conductivity was 66.2 µS. 
<superScript attach="left" box="[661,712,691,717]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">cm-1</superScript>
and dissolved oxygen was 
<quantity box="[1020,1101,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.4" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" unit="mg" value="9.4">9.4 mg</quantity>
. L- 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1135,1142,691,705]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="529">1</superScript>
(see 
<tableCitation box="[1201,1287,691,717]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="27.[151,239,705,731]" captionTargetBox="[162,2004,826,1483]" captionText="TABLE 2. Localities and environmental characteristics from stations where the species Cypricercus sp. A., Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov. and Cypricercus tiao sp. nov. were collected. Bold: type locality of the new species. PAR = Paraná, ARA = Araguaia, AMA = Amazon, PAN = Pantanal, WT = water temperature, EC = electrical conductivity, DO = dissolved oxygen, CspA = Cypricercus sp. A, Ca = Cypricercus alfredo sp. nov., Ct = Cypricercus tiao sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF78660AFFD3FF8FFF7CFD62FAFD2200" pageId="28" pageNumber="529" tableUuid="DF78660AFFD3FF8FFF7CFD62FAFD2200">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
